Interesting bash commands to not forget:

mv /flag /flag_`cat /dev/urandom | tr -dc 'a-zA-Z0-9' | fold -w 5 | head -n 1`

In this example, the commands 'tr', 'fold' and 'head'.
/dev/urandom creates random values
tr limitates the characters chosen;
fold limitates the quantity of characters;
head limitates the quantity of lines.

Maybe kaspersky utilizes something like that to generate passwords.

